<inglise> Ministers, </inglise>
<eesti> Ministrid </eesti>
<inglise> Decide to recommend that the Council for Trade in Services at its first meeting adopt the decision set out below. </inglise>
<eesti> otsustavad soovitada, et teenustekaubanduse n&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;taks oma esimesel koosolekul vastu j&auml;rgmise otsuse. </eesti>
<inglise> The Council for Trade in Services, </inglise>
<eesti> Teenustekaubanduse n&otilde;ukogu, </eesti>
<inglise> Recognizing the impact of regulatory measures relating to professional qualifications, technical standards and licensing on the expansion of trade in professional services; </inglise>
<eesti> t&otilde;dedes erialase kvalifikatsiooni, tehniliste standardite ja litsentsimisega seotud reguleerivate meetmete m&otilde;ju erialateenuste kaubanduse laiendamisele; </eesti>
<inglise> Desiring to establish multilateral disciplines with a view to ensuring that, when specific commitments are undertaken, such regulatory measures do not constitute unnecessary barriers to the supply of professional services; </inglise>
<eesti> soovides kehtestada mitmepoolsed p&otilde;him&otilde;tted, mille abil tagada, et erikohustuste v&otilde;tmisel ei kujuta sellised reguleerivad meetmed endast tarbetuid takistusi erialateenuste osutamiseks, </eesti>
<inglise> Decides as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> on teinud j&auml;rgmise otsuse: </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The work programme foreseen in paragraph 4 of Article VI on Domestic Regulation should be put into effect immediately. </inglise>
<eesti> Riigisisest reguleerimist k&auml;sitleva VI artikli l&otilde;ikes 4 ette n&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;programm tuleks viivitamata ellu viia. </eesti>
<inglise> To this end, a Working Party on Professional Services shall be established to examine and report, with recommendations, on the disciplines necessary to ensure that measures relating to qualification requirements and procedures, technical standards and licensing requirements in the field of professional services do not constitute unnecessary barriers to trade. </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks moodustatakse erialateenuste toimkond, kes uurib ja annab soovitusi, milliste p&otilde;him&otilde;tetega on vaja tagada, et kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uete ja -protseduuride, tehniliste standardite ning litsentsimisn&otilde;uetega seotud meetmed ei kujutaks endast tarbetuid kaubandust&otilde;kkeid. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> As a matter of priority, the Working Party shall make recommendations for the elaboration of multilateral disciplines in the accountancy sector, so as to give operational effect to specific commitments. </inglise>
<eesti> Esmaj&auml;rjekorras peab toimkond andma soovitusi mitmepoolsete p&otilde;him&otilde;tete v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamiseks raamatupidamisarvestuse sektoris, et erikohustused saaksid rakenduda. </eesti>
<inglise> In making these recommendations, the Working Party shall concentrate on: </inglise>
<eesti> Nende soovituste andmisel peab toimkond keskenduma j&auml;rgmistele k&uuml;simustele: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) developing multilateral disciplines relating to market access so as to ensure that domestic regulatory requirements are: (i) based on objective and transparent criteria, such as competence and the ability to supply the service; (ii) not more burdensome than necessary to ensure the quality of the service, thereby facilitating the effective liberalization of accountancy services; </inglise>
<eesti> a) turulep&auml;&auml;suga seotud mitmepoolsete p&otilde;him&otilde;tete v&auml;ljaarendamine tagamaks, et riigisisesed reguleerivad n&otilde;uded i) p&otilde;hinevad objektiivsetel ja selgetel kriteeriumidel nagu p&auml;devus ja v&otilde;ime teenust osutada; ii) ei ole koormavamad kui on vaja teenuse kvaliteedi tagamiseks, h&otilde;lbustades seega raamatupidamisarvestusteenuste t&otilde;husat liberaliseerimist; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the use of international standards and, in doing so, it shall encourage the cooperation with the relevant international organizations as defined under paragraph 5(b) of Article VI, so as to give full effect to paragraph 5 of Article VII; </inglise>
<eesti> b) rahvusvaheliste standardite kasutamine; seda tehes peab toimkond ergutama koost&ouml;&ouml;d asjaomaste rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonidega, nagu m&auml;&auml;ratletud VI artikli l&otilde;ike 5 punktis b, et t&auml;ielikult rakendada VII artikli l&otilde;ige 5; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) facilitating the effective application of paragraph 6 of Article VI of the Agreement by establishing guidelines for the recognition of qualifications. </inglise>
<eesti> c) lepingu VI artikli l&otilde;ike 6 tulemusliku kohaldamise h&otilde;lbustamine kvalifikatsiooni tunnustamise juhiste kehtestamise abil. </eesti>
<inglise> In elaborating these disciplines, the Working Party shall take account of the importance of the governmental and non-governmental bodies regulating professional services. </inglise>
<eesti> Nende p&otilde;him&otilde;tete v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamisel peab toimkond v&otilde;tma arvesse erialateenuseid reguleerivate riiklike ja mitteriiklike organite t&auml;htsust. </eesti>
 